        }

        // Wrapper implementations for all of the JSONArray methods
        @Override
        public java.lang.Object get(int index) {
            return ja.get(index);
        }

        // etcetera
    }

You don&#39;t necessarily need to write all of that by hand.  Some IDEs can automatically generate a skeleton for a wrapper class from the class that you are trying to wrap.

